caption: Delicious brunch options in an Italian rustic environment. I will visit again.
Food is delish. You will not be disappointed.

I walked past this restaurant and really wanted to try it based solely on the aesthetic. Very cozy place and comfortable. Did become a bit loud, but that didn't bother me too much, plus it was a saturday night. I had the Tagliolini ai frutti di mare and the Rapa rossa. The tagliolini was good. However what shocked me a bit was the rapa rossa. It did not come out as the menu suggested. Instead of the goat cheese and pine nuts, there was bleu cheese and no nuts, just red onions. I absolutely hate bleu cheese so this really made me upset since I LOVE beets. I think if there were to be substitutions, my party should have been informed since we would have not taken this dish and pay $13 for it.
Really enjoyed the lowkey atmosphere & the food was really good! Definitely recommend if you’re looking for authentic Italian food! 👍🏼
The best Italian restaurant I ever been. grazie mille! 👏👏❤💚

I come to this marvelous  restaurant once a month  as I love the special air that is part of this restaurant. The crew is awfuly attentive and professional. The service is certainly fast. Also, the food they cook is first-rate. I have been there many times and I was always delighted. The pay is honest. I highly recommend this restaurant to to everybody.

(Translated by Google) Nice little restaurant in Williamsburg. Cozy atmosphere .. Good products. A tiramisu to die for as seen in the American way.  (Original) Petit resto sympa à williamsburg. Ambiance cosy.. Bon produits. Un tiramisu à se damner revu à l'américaine.

We stumbled upon this place after the original place we wanted to go to had no seating. To be honest, if we knew it was Italian we may not have even of went in. Love Italian, just eat it all the time. After looking at the menu, we thought ok, classic Italian. Lets order. Welllll... The food was absolutely amazing. We just kept saing omg this is amazing after every bite. It was so freakin delicious!!! Even the dessert! Be sure to get the Warm Apple Cake. It will not disappoint. The restaurant had a nice ambiance, and the staff was very friendly. Perfect for a date or a nice dinner with friends and family. I can't wait to go back.

I really enjoyed our meal here. The portions were generous and delicious. We had a mix of pastas and pizza - every plate was cleaned by the end.  We also had a selection of the desserts. Bread and butter pudding and affogato were top notch.  The setting is warm, cosy and unpretentious, and our server was efficient and friendly.

(Translated by Google) It is a very nice place for a cozy dinner, the food was really delicious and the staff was super nice and funny, they recommended goodies which in the end also tasted very good. Italian food made and served with love, very appropriate, rustic ambience, which makes you feel much more comfortable. It is a great change between the whole fast food. The visit was really worth it and it was a good experience! We can only recommend it! A nice place in Brooklyn :)!  (Original) Es ist ein sehr schöner Ort für ein gemütliches Abendessen, das Essen war wirklich sehr sehr lecker und das Personal war super nett und lustig, sie haben uns gute Sachen empfohlen, die am Ende auch sehr gut geschmeckt haben. Italienische Speisen mit Liebe gemacht und serviert, sehr passendes, rustikales Ambiente, welches dafür sorgt, dass man sich gleich noch viel wohler fühlt. Es ist eine super Abwechslung zwischen dem ganzen Fast-food. Der Besuch hat sich wirklich gelohnt und es war eine gute Erfahrung! Wir können es nur empfehlen! Ein schöner Ort in Brooklyn : ) !

Very classic food, huge portions for cheap! If you want classic, traditional Italian food, Fiore is definitely the place to go. I personally thought it was a little bland, the seafood pasta and broccoli rabe pasta were good, but nothing special. The grilled pizza was good, but heavy on cheese so the flavor of the sauce is lost. The servers are all extremely nice and friendly, so that’s definitely a plus. All in all it was a good experience, would come again if I crave some classic Italian.

Visited Fiore the Saturday before Father's Day for brunch. Greeted by a friendly man when we arrived. We were waiting for a friend and didn't have to wait for the party to be complete before we were seated. Our server introduced himself and asked our water preference and brought us fresh bread. Once our friend arrived, we ordered a fresh mozzarella salad, burger, sea food pasta and steak special. The portions were just right and the flavor impeccable. The service, decor and beautiful weather made it an amazing experience.  TIP: For the ladies - the bathroom light is located on the lower left side of the wall when you enter 😂

Ladies and gentlemen: I'm 100% italian and I can definitely state this is the best italian restaurant I've ever been in New York City. I recommend it if you want to try the closest flavors of a typical italian kitchen. A must for italian people when they're home-sick (that's what I do). My favorites: their gnocchi with cold cuts and cheese as a starter and tagliolini ai frutti di mare as a first course. Enjoy!
